ce:section.ce:para:
The response performance of CGA to CDs was studied under optimum conditions. As shown in Fig. 5
                        a, the FL intensity of CDs gradually decreased with the increase of CGA concentration. The fluorescence quenching efficiency of CDs had a good linear relationship with CGA concentration in the range of 0.1–220 µM (Fig. 5b). The limit of detection (LOD) was 33 nM. Compared with previously published methods [11,12,20,27] (Table 1
                        ), this method possessed the advantages of simple operation, rapid response, high sensitivity, wide linear range and low LOD.
